{"sha": "721f736b1b5a6b80c58dcd302c0200e831320ec9", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOjcyMWY3MzZiMWI1YTZiODBjNThkY2QzMDJjMDIwMGU4MzEzMjBlYzk=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Corey Farwell", "email": "coreyf@rwell.org", "date": "2017-07-15T03:57:15Z"}, "committer": {"name": "GitHub", "email": "noreply@github.com", "date": "2017-07-15T03:57:15Z"}, "message": "Rollup merge of #43159 - cuviper:ptr-swap-simd, r=arielb1\n\nDisable big-endian simd in swap_nonoverlapping_bytes\n\nThis is a workaround for #42778, which was git-bisected to #40454's\noptimizations to `mem::swap`, later moved to `ptr` in #42819.  Natively\ncompiled rustc couldn't even compile stage1 libcore on powerpc64 and\ns390x, but they work fine without this `repr(simd)`.  Since powerpc64le\nworks OK, it seems probably related to being big-endian.\n\nThe underlying problem is not yet known, but this at least makes those\narchitectures functional again in the meantime.\n\ncc @arielb1", "tree": {"sha": "9ebb86e24156b95201fbf94b9f3c554934243c4c", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/9ebb86e24156b95201fbf94b9f3c554934243c4c"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/721f736b1b5a6b80c58dcd302c0200e831320ec9", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/721f736b1b5a6b80c58dcd302c0200e831320ec9", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/721f736b1b5a6b80c58dcd302c0200e831320ec9", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/721f736b1b5a6b80c58dcd302c0200e831320ec9/comments", "author": {"login": "frewsxcv", "id": 416575, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQxNjU3NQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/416575?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/frewsxcv", "html_url": "https://github.com/frewsxcv", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/frewsxcv/followers", "fol